curl - HTTP requests to internal or external APIs

Usage:
  curl [options] <url>

Options:
  -X <method>    HTTP method (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH)
  -H <header>    Add header (repeatable)
  -d <data>      Request body (use @- for stdin)
  -o <file>      Write output to file
  -i             Include response headers
  -s             Silent mode
  -v             Verbose

URL formats:
  /api/...                 Internal API (auto-authenticated)
  https://example.com      External URL

Examples:
  curl /api/data/users
  curl /api/data/users?unwrap&format=toon
  curl -X POST -d '{"name":"test"}' /api/data/users
  curl https://api.external.com/data

For queries, prefer: query (simpler, auto-formats output)
